 People with spinal cord injury (SCI) often have severe problems with management of bowel function, including incontinence, impaction, lengthy bowel routines and extremely slow transit times.

The anal irrigation system is a recently available system to help patients with bowel dysfunction empty their bowels by using pulse water irrigation.

 The system consists of a rectal balloon catheter, manual pump and water container.

